# Summary

The Leadership Reporting Model establishes a structured framework for delivering risk, compliance, governance, remediation, and third-party risk information to organizational leadership.

By providing clear visibility into enterprise risk posture, governance effectiveness, and strategic decision points, leadership can make informed decisions that support organizational objectives, regulatory compliance, and long-term resilience.
